課程概述 Course Description
       本課程旨在探討細胞生長過程中所參與的各類蛋白質在細胞生長的功能以及它們之間的相互調控關係。透過瞭解這些蛋白質活性的失調而得以瞭解致癌基因的作用。引導研究生如何研究各類生長訊息蛋白質而使得他們熟悉並具有解決生命科學領域問題的能力。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
瞭解基因與癌症的關係性瞭解基因蛋白在癌細胞作用的機制瞭解實驗設計來探討癌細胞的形成及進展 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Protein modification and protein-protein interaction2Growth factors and receptor tyrosine kinases3Heterotrimeric G proteins4Ras and its effectors5RAF, MEK, and MAPK6Nonreceptor tyrosine kinases: Src and FAK7Protein phosphatases in signal transduction8Cdc42, Rac, and Rho9Stats10Midterm Examination11Tumor suppressor gene Rb12Nuclear DNA-binding proteins: Jun,Fos,NF-B13HAT and HDAC14The role of genetic instability in p53 mutation15Wox116Aurora-A kinase17Tumor microenvironment18Final examination 

